description._content: Original Caption: Students and Teacher in a Classroom at Cathedral High School in New Ulm, Minnesota. The Town Is a County Seat Trading Center of 13,000 in a Farming Area of South Central Minnesota. It Was Founded in 1854 by a German Immigrant Land Company That Encouraged Its Kinsmen to Emigrate From Europe. Several Manufacturing Firms Have Arrived Here Since 1950 and Have Helped the Town to Grow. The Business District Was Revitalized During the 1960's.
